<div class='commentinfo comment_comment'>
2011-05-02 03:38:54 (1125 days ago)
<div id='contact-152445'>toddleigh (152445)</div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
I second Lee's comments. I walked the reach on Sunday, May 1, and the principle drop (at the &quot;Old<br/>
Dam&quot;) appeared to be solid class IV, with minimal or no eddies and at least 4 sticky holes in a<br/>
row. It will be interesting to come back with less water and see what it looks like. Also, the<br/>
gauge correlation to the nearby Jordan River gauge is unclear... however you can get recent<br/>
readings of the visual gauge from http://twitter.com/#!/GaugeLevel </div>
</td>
